2021-10-31T03:58:10Z	(#ba3fxtq) How about this: The `url` field is replaced by a `canonical` field and an `alternate` field. If the location that the client has of Feed A doesn't match what it says in Feed A's `canonical` field, the client downloads the canonical feed, Feed B, once to make sure that the location of Feed A appears in Feed B's `alternate` tags. If so, the client will continue to follow Feed A but it will use the canonical URL for hashing. As I'm typing it, though, it seems like an extremely complicated solution to a problem that isn't all that bad.
2021-10-31T04:00:17Z	(#ba3fxtq) @<prologic https://twtxt.net/user/prologic/twtxt.txt>  > Hijack it how?  Wouldn't they be able to make their own posts that would appear as having come from your account?
