2022-12-12T23:23:21Z	(#jh4n35a) @<abucci https://anthony.buc.ci/user/abucci/twtxt.txt> QR codes and link shorteners can be useful, but people have been *trained* to click and scan things without doing their due diligence. Of course, mobile operating systems make it very difficult to do so because their goal is to remove as much control as is acceptable by the user.  As far as I know, you have to load the page in a browser before you can see the entire URL, giving it the opportunity to redirect somewhere else or exploit some vulnerability on your device.  I think we agree here. When the user has no control and is taught to blindly trust these things, bad things happen.
